theorem P3_iInter_of_P3_closed
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {ι : Sort*} {S : ι → Set X}
    (hClosed : ∀ i, IsClosed (S i)) (hP3 : ∀ i, Topology.P3 (S i)) :
    Topology.P3 (⋂ i, S i) := by
  classical
  -- Each set `S i` is open because it is closed and satisfies `P3`.
  have hOpen : ∀ i, IsOpen (S i) :=
    fun i => (Topology.open_of_P3_closed (A := S i) (hClosed i)) (hP3 i)
  -- The intersection of (possibly infinitely many) open sets is open.
  have hOpenInter : IsOpen (⋂ i, S i : Set X) := by
    simpa using isOpen_iInter (fun i => hOpen i)
  -- Any open set satisfies `P3`.
  exact Topology.open_satisfies_P3 (A := ⋂ i, S i) hOpenInter

theorem Topology.subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
  intro x hxA
  -- Use the neighborhood characterization of `closure`.
  apply (mem_closure_iff).2
  intro U hU hxU
  exact ⟨x, And.intro hxU hxA⟩
